  "prompt": "Can we use 'the' before the name of any country other than Netherlands?",
  "response": "Generally, you only use \"the\" before a few specific country names:\n\n1. The Netherlands (as you mentioned)\n2. The United States\n3. The United Kingdom\n4. The Philippines\n5. The Congo\n6. The Ukraine (though this usage is debated, and many now prefer \"Ukraine\" without \"the\")\n\nFor most other countries, you do not use \"the\" before the name. For example:\n- France (not \"the France\")\n- Germany (not \"the Germany\")\n- Brazil (not \"the Brazil\")\n- China (not \"the China\")\n\nThere are some exceptions and nuances, but these are the main rules for using \"the\" with country names.",
